[ ] enforce round-trip fidelity at the text boundary $rescoped per DECISIONS.md 33: the contract is not "test every field" — types and tree-structure already own model validity. it is that three hand-maintained artifacts (formatter, tree-sitter grammar, Topiary query) agree on one wire protocol. a full proptest generator over arbitrary ActionLists is over-scoped; the real residue is reserved-char escaping, which is absent from all three layers today$ !1 +library,testing #019f26de-17cd-76f5-9f90-9d892741e8b8
    >[x] make the parser collect repeated context nodes $the multi-tag data loss (2026-07-02): parser assigned per context node, keeping only the last space-separated tag. now extends. red→green regression test in parser.rs; closes cli bug 019f268f-eb4e; comma form ruled canonical$ +library %2026-07-03T00:00 #019f26de-17cf-7e05-9d21-3bb62fa006e5
    >[x] implement reserved-char escaping (grammar, parser, formatter) with its round-trip tests $the one genuine artifact-agreement residue. DONE 2026-07-03: safe_text (name, story/charter, predecessor) and description_text now accept \\-escape sequences in the grammar; escape_field on write (link-aware — [[link]] spans copied verbatim), unescape_field on read; round-trip tests assert reserved sigils survive the formatter→Topiary→parser trip. deferred edges: context tag escaping and literal single brackets in names, both minor. this was the real !1 work the proptest generator was a proxy for$ +library,cli %2026-07-03T00:00 #019f26de-17d0-739e-a4ae-42126d9e49a0
    >[ ] fuzz the tree-sitter grammar against the relaxed parser $generated malformed input must never panic and recover-mode must never silently drop a parseable action — the relaxed-parser strict-linter decision only holds if recovery is total. the multi-tag fix above is one instance of recovery-totality; this generalizes it$ +library #019f26de-17d1-7491-8616-c8c3e8e575df
    >[ ] lint unescaped reserved sigils in freeform fields $Decision 33 ruling 2 makes an unescaped reserved char a lint warning, never a parse error — the rule does not exist yet, and doctor's first run proved the gap: dependency-hygiene carried five syntax errors from names containing hash, at-sign, and bracket sigils, degrading every load until hand-escaped 2026-07-04. W-code in core lint.rs that suggests the escaped form$ +library #019f2ec3-df5f-7095-bb03-4b9d61dd7a62
[ ] add clearhead undo backed by git snapshots $destructive commands rewrite truth immediately and fuzzy matching can pick the wrong target — wrong action plus no undo is the trust-destroying event. files-as-truth gets a time machine for free; leverage git rather than building one$ !1 +cli #019f26de-17d2-7edc-9578-b5bc873dc1f5
    >[ ] decide the snapshot mechanism and record it $auto-commit to a workspace-local repo vs a hidden ledger repo vs reusing an existing repo when the workspace is already tracked; also whether snapshots batch or land per-mutation. note the layer split with platform-model: git snapshots are mechanism-level undo (restore files); the platform_model_undo_matrix action owns semantic undo theory — this decision should acknowledge both without blocking on the theory. record in DECISIONS.md$ +cli #019f26de-17d4-7580-91d1-5ebadc129a41
    >[ ] snapshot before every mutating command $one integration point — the same choke point core-seam routes writes through; if snapshotting needs its own seam that is evidence for the write-path unification, not against it$ +cli <019f268f-eb33-7c70-b9e2-d79f46223f3d #019f26de-17d5-7c03-8f15-035f32a59cd6
    >[ ] add the undo command $restore the workspace to the pre-mutation snapshot, print what changed; redo can wait for demand$ +cli #019f26de-17d7-7c79-add2-815b8c365ea5
[ ] add idempotent cleanup commands for what doctor finds $doctor reports and never fixes, so the findings need owners. the first run surfaced the initial set: four orphaned sidecars left behind by charter archiving, five stale entries in the platform .next.json, and abandoned tmp staging files. each cleanup is an explicit idempotent command per file surface; a future doctor fix flag is sugar that invokes these commands, never fixing logic of its own$ !2 +cli #019f2ec3-df61-7e1d-8c93-e558c61dc5b3
    >[ ] make charter archiving remove the charter sidecar $archive charter moves the actions file but leaves the hidden json behind — the source of all four orphans found 2026-07-04. fixing the producer beats sweeping forever$ +cli,bug #019f2ec3-df62-7b54-812e-38660fb5a280
    >[ ] add a sidecar prune command $drop entries whose uuid matches no action in the file or its completed archive, delete whole sidecars with no actions file, and sweep orphaned tmp staging files. reads what doctor reads, fixes what doctor flags, idempotent by construction$ +cli #019f2ec3-df63-7d2b-ac86-088a5c16323d
[ ] stop deriving created timestamps from action identity $created_from_uuid reads the creation time from a uuid's top 48 bits, but that only holds for v7 — a v4 or otherwise hand-authored id makes those bits random, and 12 actions in this very workspace carry created dates between the years 5081 and 10143. they reach the RDF graph, so any recency query in the query system surfaces fiction first. the unwrap_or_else(now) guard is dead code: 48 random bits always land inside chrono's range, so from_timestamp never returns None. root cause is deriving time from identity — any id we did not mint corrupts the clock. decided 2026-07-10: keep v7 as the default and use its embedded time when genuinely present, but eat v4 gracefully by stamping the date we first see the action rather than interrogating its bits. found by doctor review, but doctor itself was blind to it — the caught-nothing case the trust charter exists to close$ !1 +library,bug #019f4d0b-7293-73ff-8da9-2c8b9ad82251
    >[ ] make created_from_uuid eat non-v7 ids $version-check before reading the timestamp bits: get_version_num() == 7 or return None, so the existing now() fallback finally fires instead of manufacturing a far-future date. this is the whole graceful-v4 fix — one guard turns the dead branch live$ +library,bug #019f4d0b-7295-7152-af2a-13941a913945
    >[ ] add a doctor check for created timestamps outside a sane window $the invariant "created is a real past date" is written down nowhere that runs — the schema types it as a string (year 8723 is a valid string), lint W005 checks the future but runs pre-hydration on the DSL while the garbage lives in the sidecar, so neither fires. a doctor finding over hydrated created (before workspace genesis or after now) is the check that would have caught all 12, and belongs with the other cross-file sidecar invariants$ +library #019f4d0b-7297-7948-a2a6-00a18dce02ff
    >[ ] restamp the already-corrupted created entries $the 12 far-future timestamps are live in committed sidecars and cannot self-heal — the guard fix only changes future stamping. one-shot correction: replace each with the honest date-we-see-it now that the derivation is fixed, so the graph stops returning fiction$ +cli #019f4d0b-7299-7d95-81c9-d976f6efe416
    >[ ] make the sidecar acts map serialize deterministically $CharterMetadata.acts is a HashMap written with to_string_pretty into a committed file, so every save reshuffles key order and produces a diff of pure noise — the working tree already carries a 13-insert/13-delete caldav sidecar churn with zero semantic change. BTreeMap keys the file by uuid string and the noise is gone for good; also makes the file a stable audit surface, which is the whole sidecar-trust point$ +library #019f4d0b-729b-71d8-967b-1f9ea1a3028d
[ ] make the standing trust decisions and record each in DECISIONS.md $these are think-once-decide-once items — decided is the deliverable, implementation may spawn its own actions later$ !2 +documentation #019f26de-17dc-7a62-8645-7cdef1a20453
    >[ ] decide the format versioning and compatibility promise $the files intend to outlive the tooling and the format already evolved once — created date moved to sidecar. decide where the version marker lives, likely workspace config, and what window the spec promises parsers will accept$ +specifications #019f26de-17dd-71b5-a9b7-798a391f4a2c
    >[ ] decide the timezone discipline $chrono Local everywhere now intersects RRULE expansion and ICS — the DST and travel bug farm. one rule, for example store with offset and expand in a workspace-declared zone, decided before the calendar work bakes in an accident$ +library #019f26de-17df-7747-bd28-d514cfdddfd8
    >[ ] decide the editor-versus-CLI concurrency story $the weekly real conflict is nvim holding a stale buffer while the CLI mutates the file underneath — the advisory lock has no editor party. decide whether the plugin watches and reloads, whether the LSP warns on external modification, or both$ +nvim,cli #019f26de-17e0-778b-960d-1ff6866d83ba
    >[ ] build the benchmark harness and set the daemon trigger $no benches exist in either crate, so the resident-daemon question has no data. synthesize a ten-thousand-action workspace, measure load, query, and save, and record the threshold at which the LSP-as-daemon shift is warranted$ +library #019f26de-17e0-757e-bb36-1df9e1bd381c
    >[ ] add platform integration CI over the pinned submodules $the only workflow deploys the vocabulary site; add a job that checks out pinned SHAs and runs grammar, core, CLI, and an nvim smoke test together so the platform repo verifies integration instead of merely recording it$ +platform #019f26de-17e2-7fac-a75a-c74830c4c637
